üß† SQL Data Types ‚Äî Complete Guide
üü© 1Ô∏è‚É£ Numeric Data Types

Used to store numbers (integers, decimals, and floating-point values).

Type	Description	Example
INT / INTEGER	Whole numbers (no decimal).	10
SMALLINT	Smaller range of integers (saves space).	100
BIGINT	Large integer values.	9876543210
TINYINT (MySQL)	Very small integer (‚Äì128 to 127).	120
DECIMAL(p, s) / NUMERIC(p, s)	Exact fixed-point numbers ‚Äî p = total digits, s = digits after decimal.	DECIMAL(10,2) ‚Üí 12345.67
FLOAT	Approximate decimal value (less precise).	3.14159
DOUBLE / REAL	Double-precision floating number.	123.456789
BIT	Binary (0 or 1).	1

üü¢ Example:

CREATE TABLE numbers_example (
    id INT,
    price DECIMAL(10,2),
    rating FLOAT,
    quantity SMALLINT
);

üü¶ 2Ô∏è‚É£ Character (String) Data Types

Used for storing text, characters, and strings.

Type	Description	Example
CHAR(n)	Fixed-length string (pads with spaces).	CHAR(5) ‚Üí 'AB' stored as 'AB '
VARCHAR(n)	Variable-length string (recommended).	VARCHAR(50) ‚Üí 'John'
TEXT / CLOB	Very long text (e.g., descriptions, comments).	'This is a long paragraph...'
NCHAR(n)	Fixed-length Unicode string.	NCHAR(10)
NVARCHAR(n)	Variable-length Unicode string.	NVARCHAR(50)

üü¢ Example:

CREATE TABLE text_example (
    first_name VARCHAR(50),
    description TEXT
);

üü® 3Ô∏è‚É£ Date & Time Data Types

Used to store dates, times, or timestamps.

Type	Description	Example
DATE	Stores only date (YYYY-MM-DD).	'2025-11-06'
TIME	Stores only time (HH:MM:SS).	'14:30:00'
DATETIME	Stores both date and time.	'2025-11-06 14:30:00'
TIMESTAMP	Similar to DATETIME but adjusts with timezone/UTC.	'2025-11-06 19:00:00'
YEAR (MySQL)	Stores year (4 digits).	2025

üü¢ Example:

CREATE TABLE datetime_example (
    created_date DATE,
    created_time TIME,
    last_updated TIMESTAMP
);

üüß 4Ô∏è‚É£ Binary Data Types

Used for images, files, or binary objects.

Type	Description	Example
BINARY(n)	Fixed-length binary data.	-
VARBINARY(n)	Variable-length binary data.	-
BLOB (Binary Large Object)	Large binary data (images, files).	-

üü¢ Example:

CREATE TABLE binary_example (
    file_id INT,
    file_data BLOB
);

üü™ 5Ô∏è‚É£ Boolean Data Type
Type	Description	Example
BOOLEAN / BOOL	Stores TRUE or FALSE (internally 1 or 0).	TRUE / FALSE

üü¢ Example:

CREATE TABLE bool_example (
    is_active BOOLEAN
);

üü´ 6Ô∏è‚É£ JSON & XML Data Types
Type	Description	Example
JSON (MySQL, PostgreSQL)	Stores JSON data (structured key-value).	'{"name": "Bala", "age": 30}'
XML (SQL Server, Oracle)	Stores XML formatted data.	<customer><name>Bala</name></customer>

üü¢ Example:

CREATE TABLE data_example (
    details JSON
);

‚ö™ 7Ô∏è‚É£ Spatial / Geometry Data Types (Advanced)

Used for geographic or geometric data.

Type	Description	Example
GEOMETRY	Any geometric shape.	POINT(10 20)
POINT	X, Y coordinates.	POINT(45.123, 67.890)
LINESTRING	Sequence of points (path).	-
POLYGON	Closed shape with multiple points.	-
‚ö´ 8Ô∏è‚É£ ENUM and SET (MySQL Only)
Type	Description	Example
ENUM('A', 'B', 'C')	One value from a predefined list.	'A'
SET('A', 'B', 'C')	Multiple values from the list.	'A,B'

üü¢ Example:

CREATE TABLE enum_example (
    status ENUM('Active', 'Inactive', 'Pending')
);

üîµ Summary Table
Category	Common Types
Numeric	INT, BIGINT, DECIMAL, FLOAT
String	CHAR, VARCHAR, TEXT
Date/Time	DATE, TIME, DATETIME, TIMESTAMP
Binary	BLOB, VARBINARY
Boolean	BOOLEAN
JSON/XML	JSON, XML
Spatial	POINT, GEOMETRY
Enumeration	ENUM, SET
